well, isn't this romantic?

07:23.580 --> 07:25.620
Thon fella's nothing
but a fly bastard!

07:25.660 --> 07:27.060
don't you be trusting him!

07:27.100 --> 07:30.100
I just want to check, does your
father think that they can hear him?

07:30.140 --> 07:31.780
Ssh.

07:31.820 --> 07:33.220
Doors clatter open

07:33.260 --> 07:34.820
apologies, folks.

07:34.860 --> 07:37.340
We've just had
a wee security alert there.

07:37.380 --> 07:38.420
Grumbling

07:38.460 --> 07:41.620
I'm afraid we're gonna have
to carry out a wee evacuation.

07:41.660 --> 07:43.620
So, if you'll all follow me.

07:43.660 --> 07:45.860
Lovely. Great stuff.

07:45.900 --> 07:48.340
That's the last time
i let you organise a night out.

07:48.380 --> 07:49.620
Ok, then.

07:49.660 --> 07:51.420
What about this keyser soze fella?

07:51.460 --> 07:53.220
Who's keyser soze?

07:53.260 --> 07:54.980
Exactly!

07:55.020 --> 07:58.300
Music: don't give me your life
by Alex party

08:01.580 --> 08:04.980
{an5}god, this whole
writing-from-the-soul carry-on
is a nightmare.

08:05.020 --> 08:06.620
I know. What rhymes with ride?

08:06.660 --> 08:07.660
Bide.

08:07.700 --> 08:10.700
Bide? What the fuck does bide mean?
Bide. That's not a word.

08:10.740 --> 08:11.780
It is a word, Michelle.

08:11.820 --> 08:13.620
Bide? You've pure made that up.

08:13.660 --> 08:15.140
Can we all be quiet? Please.

08:15.180 --> 08:16.740
What do you think, James?

08:16.780 --> 08:19.020
You've got red eyes
cos I ran out of brown.

08:19.060 --> 08:20.220
My eyes are green.

08:20.260 --> 08:21.300
Now you tell me.

08:22.500 --> 08:24.180
Ok. So, I'm trying
not to think too much.

08:24.220 --> 08:25.820
Just to sort of
let it flow through me.

08:25.860 --> 08:27.420
That's minging, Erin.

08:27.460 --> 08:28.900
Here's what I have so far.

08:28.940 --> 08:30.340
"You know we belong together

08:30.380 --> 08:31.740
"you and I forever and ever

08:31.780 --> 08:34.179
"no matter where you are
you're my guiding star."

08:34.220 --> 08:36.419
Isn't that the theme tune
to home and away?

08:36.460 --> 08:37.820
Is it?

08:37.860 --> 08:39.539
Aw, for god's sake!

08:39.580 --> 08:40.780
Door opens

08:40.820 --> 08:41.940
shit!

08:41.980 --> 08:44.059
Gerry: My money's on
Alec Baldwin's brother.

08:44.100 --> 08:45.660
Mary: It's Gabriel byrne.
I'm telling you.

08:45.700 --> 08:47.500
Joe: The fella with the bad leg
said it wasn't, Mary.

08:47.540 --> 08:50.980
The fella with the bad leg's
covering for him, da!

08:51.020 --> 08:53.700
Sweet Jesus.

08:53.740 --> 08:55.260
Mouth full: Mammy, we can explain.

08:55.300 --> 08:56.660
Not the Christmas cupboard?

08:56.700 --> 08:58.700
They've had
the very tunnock's, Mary.

08:58.740 --> 08:59.900
Animals, the lot of you!

08:59.940 --> 09:01.460
We needed energy for our poetry.

09:01.500 --> 09:03.500
I'll give you
energy for your poetry!

09:03.540 --> 09:05.980
We were just gonna take
a handful of chocolate money, Mary.

09:06.020 --> 09:07.420
But then one thing led to another.

09:07.460 --> 09:09.020
What am I supposed to do?

09:09.060 --> 09:10.300
I'll have to start from scratch now.

09:10.340 --> 09:11.980
And December's only round
the corner.

09:12.020 --> 09:13.300
It's eight months away, love.

09:13.340 --> 09:15.780
This suits you, doesn't it?
I'm sorry?

09:15.820 --> 09:17.900
I've seen you eyeing up
that Christmas cupboard.

09:17.940 --> 09:20.180
You hoked about in there
long before the wains did.

09:20.220 --> 09:21.740
I'll stake my life on it.

09:21.780 --> 09:24.820
That is simply not true.

09:24.860 --> 09:26.980
Let's just salvage what we can.

09:27.020 --> 09:29.340
There's only a couple
of snowballs left, Mary.

09:29.380 --> 09:31.340
It's been an absolute free-for-all.

09:31.380 --> 09:33.100
Your mothers will be
hearing about this.

09:33.140 --> 09:35.260
Aw, for... what got into you, girls?

09:35.300 --> 09:37.860
You know you don't touch
the Christmas cupboard.

09:37.900 --> 09:39.140
We're stressed!

09:39.180 --> 09:41.500
Our new English teacher made us
rip up all our poems

09:41.540 --> 09:42.860
and re-do them in one night.

09:42.900 --> 09:44.060
Who is this blow-in?

09:44.100 --> 09:45.300
Here name's miss de brun.

09:45.340 --> 09:47.300
She's a bit of a bitch,
but, cracking eyeliner.

09:47.340 --> 09:48.500
Winged or smudged?

09:48.540 --> 09:49.780
Sort of both.

09:49.820 --> 09:51.100
Interesting.

09:51.140 --> 09:52.620
She ripped up your poems?

09:52.660 --> 09:54.180
She said we weren't
writing from the soul.

09:54.220 --> 09:56.900
Well, why in under god
weren't you writing from the soul?

09:56.940 --> 09:58.020
Seriously?

09:59.060 --> 10:01.740
Miss de brun: It was difficult,
so you've just given up?

10:01.780 --> 10:03.900
You might fail,
so why bother trying?

10:03.940 --> 10:04.980
Exactly.

10:05.940 --> 10:08.060
Told you she'd understand.

10:08.100 --> 10:11.460
Have you ever stopped
to look at these?

10:11.500 --> 10:13.700
These faces from the past.

10:15.820 --> 10:18.140
They're not
so different from you, really.

10:18.180 --> 10:21.020
They had dreams like you do.

10:21.060 --> 10:23.540
They had...Ambitions.

10:23.580 --> 10:25.140
But now, they're gone.

10:26.420 --> 10:27.700
Dead.

10:28.860 --> 10:30.420
Dust.

10:30.460 --> 10:32.900
That's my auntie Anne third
from the left. She's not dead.

10:32.940 --> 10:34.460
Ssh! But she's only 54.

10:34.500 --> 10:37.180
She runs the mobile library
in ballymagroarty. Quiet.

10:37.220 --> 10:41.460
But did they fulfil those dreams,
those ambitions?

10:41.500 --> 10:45.980
One day, girls, you too will just be
an old photograph in a hallway.

10:47.540 --> 10:49.660
You only get one life.

10:51.700 --> 10:53.020
don't be afraid to live it.

10:54.620 --> 10:55.740
Find your voice.

10:57.620 --> 10:59.660
Make your mark.

11:01.140 --> 11:03.180
Sometimes

11:03.220 --> 11:07.980
the river flows
but nothing breathes

11:08.020 --> 11:12.020
a train arrives
but never leaves...

11:12.060 --> 11:16.180
Dig deep, something you hate,
something you despise.

11:16.220 --> 11:18.460
No holding back. Come on!

11:18.500 --> 11:19.740
Get it out!

11:20.780 --> 11:23.180
Injustice! Yes!

11:23.220 --> 11:24.500
Prejudice!

11:24.540 --> 11:26.620
Good! This is good!

11:26.660 --> 11:29.620
Of being rich or being poor

11:29.660 --> 11:32.340
such a shame...

11:32.380 --> 11:34.500
Mass! Come on!

11:34.540 --> 11:36.580
My own socks!

11:36.620 --> 11:38.180
Ok.

11:38.220 --> 11:39.980
Being late for school!

11:40.020 --> 11:41.740
Piano lessons!

11:41.780 --> 11:44.140
The fact that people here
use the word "wee"

11:44.180 --> 11:47.460
to describe things that aren't
even actually that small!

11:47.500 --> 11:50.020
God, but I love that accent, James!

11:50.060 --> 11:52.500
Just seek yourself
and you will shine

11:54.020 --> 11:57.700
you've go to search for
the hero inside yourself

11:59.740 --> 12:02.340
search for the secrets you hide

12:04.340 --> 12:07.260
search for
the hero inside yourself

12:09.020 --> 12:11.900
until you find
the key to your life.

12:17.100 --> 12:19.140
I've got the key
I've got the secret...

12:19.180 --> 12:22.060
Miss de brun's amazing.
I've just never met anyone like her.

12:22.100 --> 12:24.300
She's an inspiration. Absolutely.

12:24.340 --> 12:27.300
She really knows how to grab
things by the balls. Yeah!

12:27.340 --> 12:29.220
She's changed my life,
she really has.

12:29.260 --> 12:30.780
She likes my accent.

12:30.820 --> 12:33.740
I'd die for her.
I think I would too, you know.

12:33.780 --> 12:35.780
Me too. Aye. Fuck it. Why not?

12:35.820 --> 12:38.580
Yeah! I mean, obviously, I totally
agree, I'd die for her as well.

12:38.620 --> 12:40.420
But I'm also conscious of the fact

12:40.460 --> 12:42.940
we've only known her,
like, two days. And?

12:42.980 --> 12:45.420
Is it a wee bit weird she's
invited us to her house at night?

12:45.460 --> 12:47.100
What do you mean?
Well, she's a teacher.

12:47.140 --> 12:48.500
She's much more than a teacher.

12:48.540 --> 12:50.460
Yeah. No. Obviously.
I get that. She's great.

12:50.500 --> 12:53.380
But it's just that I have a feeling
it might be, sort of, frowned upon.

12:53.420 --> 12:56.020
God, Clare. You're so conditioned.
What's that supposed to mean?

12:56.060 --> 12:57.620
It means you need to
loosen the fuck up.

12:57.660 --> 12:59.740
I am loose, thank you very much.

12:59.780 --> 13:01.780
Face it, Clare,
you're a craic killer.

13:01.820 --> 13:02.940
I'm not a craic killer.

13:05.100 --> 13:07.420
I am not a craic killer!

13:07.460 --> 13:09.740
Some wine?
No. Actually, I don't...

13:11.220 --> 13:12.460
Cheers.

13:16.740 --> 13:18.620
Hit me again. Ok.

13:19.860 --> 13:21.620
You don't have much stuff.

13:21.660 --> 13:24.420
Everything I own
can fit into a suitcase.

13:24.460 --> 13:27.580
I've never understood why
people weigh themselves down with

13:27.620 --> 13:29.140
meaningless crap, you know?

13:29.180 --> 13:31.220
Yeah. God, I just hate possessions
so much.

13:31.260 --> 13:34.180
Does that mean I can have
your sylvanian family collection?

13:34.220 --> 13:37.780
Shut up, orla. I don't like
to feel tied down, you know.

13:37.820 --> 13:41.780
Life should be spontaneous, free.

13:41.820 --> 13:42.900
Big time.

13:42.940 --> 13:44.660
Slainte.

13:44.700 --> 13:47.540
This is actually nice.
It tastes a bit like blood.

