"It is a sort of splendid torch,

13:53.020 --> 13:57.260
"which I have got hold of for the
moment, and I want to make it burn

13:57.300 --> 13:59.180
"as brightly as possible."

14:00.260 --> 14:01.420
That's beautiful.

14:01.460 --> 14:03.140
Shaw.

14:03.180 --> 14:04.540
It's my favourite quote.

14:04.580 --> 14:06.460
Take it easy, Oliver Reed.

14:06.500 --> 14:07.580
What's yours?

14:07.620 --> 14:10.740
"Be careful, child,
of the doll made of glass.

14:10.780 --> 14:14.420
"For if you hold her too tightly,
she will break, and you will bleed."

14:14.460 --> 14:17.220
I don't think I'm familiar
with that one. Who's it by?

14:17.260 --> 14:19.460
Me. It's by me. Wow!

14:19.500 --> 14:23.140
This is the rhythm
of the night...

14:23.180 --> 14:25.060
I feel all floaty.

14:25.100 --> 14:27.100
She's absolutely fucking flying.

14:27.140 --> 14:30.380
Well, well, well.
What are you guys up to?

14:30.420 --> 14:31.540
Nothing much.

14:31.580 --> 14:33.700
We've just been hanging out
at miss de brun's place.

14:33.740 --> 14:35.540
You were at her house? At night?

14:35.580 --> 14:37.660
Well, that's a bit inappropriate.

14:37.700 --> 14:39.340
Your ma is a bit inappropriate.

14:39.380 --> 14:42.060
That doesn't even make sense.
Your ma doesn't even make sense.

14:42.100 --> 14:43.620
Is she drunk? Your ma's drunk.

14:43.660 --> 14:45.660
Ok, Clare. I think we get the idea.

14:45.700 --> 14:47.820
Lovely seeing you, Jenny.
Take care now.

14:50.420 --> 14:52.660
Radio chatter

14:57.380 --> 15:00.380
I never slept a wink last night,
you know. Me either.

15:00.420 --> 15:02.020
Keyser soze? Naw.

15:02.060 --> 15:04.580
I went to bed with my rollers in.
Sure, it's always a nightmare.

15:04.620 --> 15:07.260
Then why do you do it?
I've no volume at the root, Mary.

15:07.300 --> 15:08.340
What choice do I have?

15:08.380 --> 15:10.260
I'm leaning towards
Pete postlethwaite now.

15:10.300 --> 15:13.020
It wasn't Pete postlethwaite, da.
It's never Pete postlethwaite.

15:13.060 --> 15:14.740
Look, this is
driving me to distraction.

15:14.780 --> 15:15.980
We'll have to go back tonight.

15:16.020 --> 15:17.780
It's not in the listings any more.
What?

15:17.820 --> 15:19.940
The cinema's stopped showing it.
Well done.

15:19.980 --> 15:22.180
It's not my fault.
Sure, nothing ever is.

15:22.220 --> 15:24.700
What are we meant to do? Wait for
them to release it on video.

15:24.740 --> 15:27.700
I can't, Gerry!
I can't go on like this!

15:27.740 --> 15:28.860
I need to know!

15:28.900 --> 15:30.020
Well, that's us away.

15:30.060 --> 15:33.380
Where's your socks, love?
They're just not for me, mammy.

15:33.420 --> 15:35.500
I'm sorry. You'll be foundered.

15:35.540 --> 15:38.300
I know what I'm doing.
Have a great day, everyone.

15:38.340 --> 15:39.860
What are you in
such a good mood about?

15:39.900 --> 15:42.020
Just, you know, life.

15:42.060 --> 15:45.260
You're up to something.
And I'll get to the bottom of it.

15:45.300 --> 15:49.180
Honest to god, Erin - between you
and keyser soze, my head is turned.

15:49.220 --> 15:50.380
Who's keyser soze?

15:50.420 --> 15:51.740
God almighty!

15:56.460 --> 15:58.220
Take a seat, please, ladies.

15:59.540 --> 16:01.340
Where's miss de brun? Gone.

16:01.380 --> 16:03.500
And she's not coming back. What?

16:03.540 --> 16:05.620
I knew it. When I woke up
this morning, I had a feeling

16:05.660 --> 16:08.340
something terrible was going to
happen and also that essentially

16:08.380 --> 16:09.860
deep down, I'm quite an evil person.

16:09.900 --> 16:12.220
It's called a hangover, Clare.
You'll be grand.

16:12.260 --> 16:15.140
I will be taking this class
for the rest of the term,

16:15.180 --> 16:17.900
which makes me want to pull off
my own face, but needs must.

16:17.940 --> 16:19.420
This was you, wasn't it?

16:19.460 --> 16:21.540
What did you do? What did you say?

16:21.580 --> 16:23.300
I don't know what
you're talking about.

16:23.340 --> 16:24.700
Aye, so you don't. Supergrass!

16:24.740 --> 16:27.420
That's quite enough.
You don't understand, sister.

16:27.460 --> 16:30.180
Miss de brun, she touched us.

16:30.220 --> 16:33.180
What? She made us think,
she made us feel.

16:33.220 --> 16:34.300
Thank god.

16:35.460 --> 16:38.300
That would be all I need.
You can't sack her! You just can't!

16:38.340 --> 16:42.780
Miss Quinn, you appear to be
under the misapprehension

16:42.820 --> 16:45.940
that you can address me
as though you are my equal.

16:45.980 --> 16:48.460
I suggest you rein it in
and take a seat.

16:52.180 --> 16:53.900
School bell rings

16:56.900 --> 16:58.060
what if she's in there?

16:58.100 --> 17:00.660
It's Friday. She's at judo.
Relax the kecks, Clare.

17:08.700 --> 17:10.300
Creepy wee fucker, isn't he?

17:10.339 --> 17:12.900
I would just like to just state
once again for the record

17:12.940 --> 17:15.540
that I think this might be
the worst idea we've ever had.

17:15.579 --> 17:17.380
Look, do you want to help
miss de brun or not?

17:17.420 --> 17:18.619
Can we not find a way to help her

17:18.660 --> 17:20.619
that doesn't involve
abducting a holy statue?

17:20.660 --> 17:23.579
We're not abducting him, Clare -
we're kidnapping him.

17:23.619 --> 17:25.819
Is that different?
I don't think that's different.

17:25.859 --> 17:27.300
We'll give him back on the condition

17:27.339 --> 17:29.140
that miss de brun
is rightfully reinstated.

17:29.180 --> 17:31.580
I'm sure sister Michael
will be fully on board with that.

17:31.620 --> 17:33.300
Aye, me too.
Ok, let's do the photograph.

17:33.340 --> 17:35.140
Great. I'll write the ransom note.

17:35.180 --> 17:37.700
We need a copy of today's newspaper.
Why?

17:37.740 --> 17:40.780
It's just the done thing,
kidnapping-wise.

17:40.820 --> 17:43.700
I've got last week's
parish bulletin. That'll do.

17:43.740 --> 17:45.020
I'm going to use my left hand,

17:45.060 --> 17:47.060
just in case she recognises
my handwriting.

17:47.100 --> 17:49.100
Well, this is foolproof!

17:49.140 --> 17:51.900
Should I start,
"dear sister Michael,"

17:51.940 --> 17:54.860
or "to whom it may concern,"
do you think?

17:54.900 --> 17:57.660
I don't know about this one.
I think he looks a bit fat in it.

17:57.700 --> 17:59.180
Yeah, that's not flattering. Aye.

18:00.140 --> 18:01.900
Maybe if we just tilt him
this way a bit...

18:01.940 --> 18:03.780
See, I think he needs to
come forward a bit.

18:03.820 --> 18:05.100
It was fine where it was, dicko.

18:05.140 --> 18:08.060
Look, I'm the one taking the photo.
Fuck off! Just leave it, Michelle.

18:08.100 --> 18:09.740
Smashing

18:09.780 --> 18:12.220
good god.

18:14.420 --> 18:18.460
Ok, so we've gone
a bit off course here.

18:18.500 --> 18:20.180
Let's glue him! Brilliant.

18:20.220 --> 18:22.660
We'll just...
We'll just stick it back on.

18:22.700 --> 18:24.740
We'll stick it back on,
and it'll all be grand.

18:28.060 --> 18:30.260
Excited chatter

18:30.300 --> 18:32.500
Jesus, girls!
What are you still doing here?

18:32.540 --> 18:33.940
I thought we had an intruder.

18:33.980 --> 18:36.900
And I tell you what -
he'd have been a sorry boy,

18:36.940 --> 18:39.420
for I just nailed
some serious moves.

18:42.260 --> 18:45.140
We were just working on
our English project, sister.

18:47.380 --> 18:48.500
Step aside.

18:49.620 --> 18:50.820
She snaps her fingers

19:00.660 --> 19:02.780
what in god's name have you done?

19:02.820 --> 19:03.980
Camera whirs

19:05.340 --> 19:08.100
how could you have glued his head on
upside down, orla?

19:08.140 --> 19:11.180
He's wearing a hat,
for Christ's sake! Quiet!

19:11.220 --> 19:12.940
All right, Mary, Sarah, deidre.

19:12.980 --> 19:15.140
Your girls involved in
this beheading too, then?

19:15.180 --> 19:18.300
It wasn't me, mammy!
Do not speak to me, Clare.

19:18.340 --> 19:19.780
In fact, don't even breathe.

19:21.060 --> 19:22.820
Take a seat, mrs devlin.

19:25.660 --> 19:29.340
The statue was
stolen from this room,

19:29.380 --> 19:31.860
so I've asked miss mooney
to photograph the scene.

19:31.900 --> 19:36.220
Either it is replaced, at your
expense, or the school will sue.

19:36.260 --> 19:37.580
To be honest, sister,

19:37.620 --> 19:40.980
and I'm not just saying this -

19:41.020 --> 19:42.620
I think he looks better.

19:42.660 --> 19:44.700
He looks like
his head's on upside down.

19:45.820 --> 19:48.980
And I'll be suspending them
for a week. Please, god! No!

19:49.020 --> 19:51.460
A week? We're going to be stuck
with them for a week?

19:51.500 --> 19:53.700
Be reasonable, sister!
We didn't behead the fella.

19:53.740 --> 19:56.380
By Christ, you're in for it, Erin.
It was an accident, mammy.

19:56.420 --> 19:58.980
So you accidentally wrote
a ransom note, did you?

19:59.020 --> 20:00.980
Ok, that bit wasn't an accident.

20:01.020 --> 20:04.020
But we were so upset by
what happened to miss de brun.

20:04.060 --> 20:06.220
It was wrong.
She shouldn't have been sacked.

20:06.260 --> 20:07.620
She wasn't. What?

20:07.660 --> 20:09.700
Knock on door

20:09.740 --> 20:10.980
sorry to interrupt, sister.

20:11.020 --> 20:14.700
But if I could just grab the old
p45, then I'll be out of your way.

20:14.740 --> 20:15.980
Excuse me?

20:16.020 --> 20:18.620
Miss de brun has
decided to leave us.

20:18.660 --> 20:21.100
I got offered a post
in st Dominic's girls.

20:21.140 --> 20:24.700
Better wages, holiday pay,
great pension - the works.

20:24.740 --> 20:26.140
I couldn't say no, really.

20:26.180 --> 20:28.700
But what happened to
living for the moment?

20:28.740 --> 20:31.020
What happened to
"life should be spontaneous"?

20:31.060 --> 20:32.900
Yeah, I know,
but I'm buying a house

20:32.940 --> 20:35.500
and the mortgage rates are
absolutely crippling at the minute.

20:35.540 --> 20:37.180
Tell me about it. Desperate.

20:37.220 --> 20:40.460
Part of the reason
i became a nun - free accommodation.

20:40.500 --> 20:44.180
But, miss de brun, you inspired me
to do my greatest work.

20:44.220 --> 20:46.460
I see. Which was?

20:46.500 --> 20:49.260
My poem. My glass doll poem.
She's a doll made of glass.

20:49.300 --> 20:51.300
She's a glass doll.
I read it to you last night.

20:51.340 --> 20:53.940
Yeah. I wasn't really
listening, to be honest.

20:55.060 --> 20:56.740
Cheers.

20:58.260 --> 20:59.700
Carpe diem.

21:00.940 --> 21:02.620
Carpe dickhead.

21:03.940 --> 21:07.060
Well, I guess we never knew
who the real miss de brun was.

21:07.100 --> 21:08.260
A bit like keyser soze.

21:08.300 --> 21:09.900
The fella with the bad leg.

21:09.940 --> 21:11.860
What? Keyser soze.

21:12.860 --> 21:14.620
He was the fella with the bad leg.

21:14.660 --> 21:16.580
He was talking
absolute shite the whole time.

21:16.620 --> 21:20.700
He was one of those...Er, what do
you call it? Unreliable narrators.

21:23.180 --> 21:24.580
That's very clever.

21:24.620 --> 21:26.780
Yeah. I thought so, too.

21:28.820 --> 21:30.380
Look this way, girls.

21:33.140 --> 21:35.540
Here we go again

21:35.580 --> 21:38.260
here we go-go-go
to the temple of consumption

21:38.300 --> 21:39.940
get your gear and start to spend

21:39.980 --> 21:42.540
here we go-go-go
with a total dedication

21:42.580 --> 21:44.620
here we go again

21:44.660 --> 21:47.060
here we go-go-go
to the temple of consumption

21:47.100 --> 21:49.300
get your gear and start to spend

21:49.340 --> 21:52.460
here we go,
here we go, here we go.

21:56.260 --> 21:58.540
As some sort of prototype
i serve to be

21:58.580 --> 22:01.100
you see, tomorrow's dream
has never been part of me...

